### Terroir.ma — All 12 User Manual Test Scenarios
### VS Code REST Client (humao.rest-client) / IntelliJ HTTP Client
### Base URL: http://localhost:3000
### Auth: POST token request first, copy access_token into @token variables

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@keycloakUrl = http://localhost:8080/realms/terroir-ma/protocol/openid-connect/token
@clientId = terroir-portal

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AUTH — Get tokens for each persona (run these first)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Khalid (super-admin)
# @name khalidAuth
POST {{keycloakUrl}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username=khalid&password=Terroir2025!

@khalidToken = {{khalidAuth.response.body.$.access_token}}

###

### Fatima (cooperative-admin)
# @name fatimaAuth
POST {{keycloakUrl}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username=fatima&password=Terroir2025!

@fatimaToken = {{fatimaAuth.response.body.$.access_token}}

###

### Hassan (cooperative-member)
# @name hassanAuth
POST {{keycloakUrl}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username=hassan&password=Terroir2025!

@hassanToken = {{hassanAuth.response.body.$.access_token}}

###

### Dr. Amina (lab-technician)
# @name aminaAuth
POST {{keycloakUrl}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username=amina&password=Terroir2025!

@aminaToken = {{aminaAuth.response.body.$.access_token}}

###

### Youssef (inspector)
# @name youssefAuth
POST {{keycloakUrl}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username=youssef&password=Terroir2025!

@youssefToken = {{youssefAuth.response.body.$.access_token}}

###

### Omar (certification-body)
# @name omarAuth
POST {{keycloakUrl}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username=omar&password=Terroir2025!

@omarToken = {{omarAuth.response.body.$.access_token}}

###

### Leila (customs-agent)
# @name leilaAuth
POST {{keycloakUrl}}
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&client_id={{clientId}}&username=leila&password=Terroir2025!

@leilaToken = {{leilaAuth.response.body.$.access_token}}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SCENARIO 1 — SUPER-ADMIN: Platform Setup & Oversight (Khalid)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### S1.1 — Platform Dashboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}

###

### S1.2 — List Pending Cooperatives
GET {{baseUrl}}/cooperatives?status=pending
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}

###

### S1.3 — Verify a Cooperative (replace :id with real UUID)
@coopId = coop-uuid-001
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/cooperatives/{{coopId}}/verify
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}

###

### S1.4 — Create a Laboratory
# @name createLab
POST {{baseUrl}}/labs
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Laboratoire ONSSA Agadir",
  "onssaAccreditationNumber": "ONSSA-LAB-2025-AGD-007",
  "city": "Agadir",
  "region": "SOUSS_MASSA"
}

@labId = {{createLab.response.body.$.id}}

###

### S1.5 — Accredit the Laboratory
POST {{baseUrl}}/labs/{{labId}}/accredit
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}

###

### S1.6 — Update Campaign Settings
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/admin/settings/campaign
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentCampaignYear": "2025/2026",
  "campaignStartMonth": 10,
  "campaignStartDay": 1
}

###

### S1.7 — View Audit Logs
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/audit-logs?page=1&limit=20&from=2025-11-01
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}

###

### S1.8 — View Kafka DLQ Stats
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/kafka/dlq-stats
Authorization: Bearer {{khalidToken}}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SCENARIO 2 — COOPERATIVE-ADMIN: Full Cooperative Setup (Fatima)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### S2.1 — View My Cooperative Profile (replace with real coop UUID from JWT)
@myCoop = 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
GET {{baseUrl}}/cooperatives/{{myCoop}}
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}

###

### S2.2 — Add a Member
# @name addMember
POST {{baseUrl}}/cooperatives/{{myCoop}}/members
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Hassan Oubella",
  "fullNameAr": "حسن أوبيلة",
  "cin": "J123456",
  "phone": "+212662345678",
  "email": "hassan@coop-safran.ma",
  "role": "member"
}

###

### S2.3 — Register a Farm with GPS
# @name addFarm
POST {{baseUrl}}/cooperatives/{{myCoop}}/farms
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Parcelle Nord Taliouine — Lot 3",
  "areaHectares": 2.5,
  "cropTypes": ["SAFFRON"],
  "regionCode": "DRAA_TAFILALET",
  "commune": "Taliouine",
  "latitude": 30.5321,
  "longitude": -7.9241
}

@farmId = {{addFarm.response.body.$.id}}

###

### S2.4 — Update Cooperative Profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/cooperatives/{{myCoop}}
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "fatima@coop-safran-taliouine.ma",
  "phone": "+212661234567",
  "address": "Douar Ait Ouagane, Taliouine, 83300"
}

###

### S2.5 — View My Certifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/certifications/my
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}

###

### S2.6 — Update SMS Notification Preference
PUT {{baseUrl}}/notifications/preferences/me
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "channel": "sms", "isEnabled": true }


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SCENARIO 3 — COOPERATIVE-MEMBER: Harvest & Batch Logging (Hassan)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### S3.1 — Log a Harvest
# @name logHarvest
POST {{baseUrl}}/harvests
Authorization: Bearer {{hassanToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "farmId": "{{farmId}}",
  "productTypeCode": "SAFFRON",
  "quantityKg": 12.5,
  "harvestDate": "2025-10-28",
  "campaignYear": "2025/2026",
  "method": "Cueillette manuelle des pistils — récolte à l'aube",
  "metadata": {
    "pickerCount": 8,
    "weatherCondition": "sunny",
    "altitudeM": 1650
  }
}

@harvestId = {{logHarvest.response.body.$.id}}

###

### S3.2 — Create a Production Batch
# @name createBatch
POST {{baseUrl}}/batches
Authorization: Bearer {{hassanToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productTypeCode": "SAFFRON",
  "harvestIds": ["{{harvestId}}"],
  "totalQuantityKg": 12.5,
  "processingDate": "2025-10-29"
}

@batchId = {{createBatch.response.body.$.id}}

###

### S3.3a — Add DRYING Processing Step
POST {{baseUrl}}/batches/{{batchId}}/processing-steps
Authorization: Bearer {{hassanToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "stepType": "DRYING",
  "doneAt": "2025-10-29T08:00:00Z",
  "notes": "Séchage à l'ombre pendant 3 jours — humidité ambiante 42%"
}

###

### S3.3b — Add SORTING Processing Step
POST {{baseUrl}}/batches/{{batchId}}/processing-steps
Authorization: Bearer {{hassanToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "stepType": "SORTING",
  "doneAt": "2025-11-01T09:00:00Z",
  "notes": "Tri manuel — sélection Grade 1 uniquement, couleur rouge >80%"
}

###

### S3.3c — Add PACKAGING Processing Step
POST {{baseUrl}}/batches/{{batchId}}/processing-steps
Authorization: Bearer {{hassanToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "stepType": "PACKAGING",
  "doneAt": "2025-11-02T14:00:00Z",
  "notes": "Conditionnement en sachets hermétiques 1g — ref PKG-SAF-001"
}

###

### S3.4 — View Processing History
GET {{baseUrl}}/batches/{{batchId}}/processing-steps
Authorization: Bearer {{hassanToken}}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SCENARIO 4 — LAB TECHNICIAN: Lab Test (Dr. Amina)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### S4.1 — Submit Lab Test (by Fatima)
# @name submitLabTest
POST {{baseUrl}}/lab-tests
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchId": "{{batchId}}",
  "laboratoryId": "{{labId}}",
  "expectedResultDate": "2025-11-15"
}

@labTestId = {{submitLabTest.response.body.$.id}}

###

### S4.2 — View Assigned Tests (Dr. Amina)
GET {{baseUrl}}/lab-tests?status=submitted
Authorization: Bearer {{aminaToken}}

###

### S4.3 — Record Analysis Results (ISO 3632 — Saffron)
# @name recordResults
POST {{baseUrl}}/lab-tests/{{labTestId}}/results
Authorization: Bearer {{aminaToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "testValues": {
    "crocin_e440": 247,
    "safranal_e330": 34,
    "picrocrocin_e257": 82,
    "moisture_pct": 8.5,
    "ash_total_pct": 5.2
  },
  "technicianName": "Dr. Amina Benali"
}

###

### S4.5 — Get Lab Test Result
GET {{baseUrl}}/lab-tests/{{labTestId}}/result
Authorization: Bearer {{aminaToken}}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SCENARIO 5 — INSPECTOR: Field Inspection (Youssef)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### S5.1 — View My Assigned Inspections
GET {{baseUrl}}/inspections/my
Authorization: Bearer {{youssefToken}}

###

### S6.1 — Fatima Requests Certification (needed before inspection steps)
# @name requestCert
POST {{baseUrl}}/certifications/request
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchId": "{{batchId}}",
  "certificationType": "IGP"
}

@certId = {{requestCert.response.body.$.id}}

###

### S6.2 — Start Document Review (Omar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/start-review
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "remarks": "Documentation complete" }

###

### S6.3 — Schedule Inspection (Omar)
# @name scheduleInspection
POST {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/schedule-inspection
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "certificationId": "{{certId}}",
  "inspectorId": "youssef-user-uuid",
  "scheduledDate": "2025-11-20",
  "farmIds": ["{{farmId}}"]
}

###

### S5.2 — Start Field Visit (Youssef)
POST {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/start-inspection
Authorization: Bearer {{youssefToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### S5.3 — Complete Inspection (via certification endpoint)
POST {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/complete-inspection
Authorization: Bearer {{youssefToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "passed": true,
  "summary": "Visite terrain effectuée le 20/11/2025. Parcelle Lot 3 conforme aux exigences IGP Drâa-Tafilalet."
}


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### SCENARIO 6 — CERTIFICATION BODY: Full Decision Workflow (Omar)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### S6.5 — Start Final Review
POST {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/start-final-review
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### S6.6 — Grant Certification
# @name grantCert
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/grant
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "validFrom": "2025-11-25",
  "validUntil": "2026-11-25"
}

###

### S6.7 — Download Trilingual PDF Certificate
GET {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/certificate.pdf
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}

###

### S6.8 — Download QR Code PNG
GET {{baseUrl}}/qr-codes/{{certId}}/download?format=png
Authorization: Bearer {{fatimaToken}}

###

### S6.9 — Certification Analytics
GET {{baseUrl}}/certifications/analytics?from=2025-01-01&to=2026-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}

###

### S6.10 — Deny Certification (alternative flow, different cert)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/deny
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Paramètre picrocrocine en dessous du seuil minimum IGP (valeur mesurée: 62, seuil: 70)."
}

###

### S6.11 — Revoke a Granted Certification
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/certifications/{{certId}}/revoke
Authorization: Bearer {{omarToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reason": "Contrôle de marché : échantillon ne correspond pas aux paramètres certifiés."
}


